Note:
Markdown Translation Round-Trip Probe

End-to-end proof that the Markdown translation pipeline is REAL, not a skeleton:

    Markdown source
      -> markdown_lexer  (tokenize: ATX headings, fences, list markers, inline)
      -> markdown_parser (build Markdown block/inline AST)
      -> markdown_to_hir (lower AST to canonical HIR dictionary/array literal model)
      -> hir_to_markdown (emit HIR back to CommonMark text)

The probe feeds a representative document containing a level-2 ATX heading, a
paragraph carrying emphasis and inline code, an unordered list with two items,
a fenced code block with a language tag, and a link. It then:

  1. Translates the source to HIR and asserts the HIR root is the document
     dictionary literal, walks its block children, and checks each block's
     structured attributes: heading level + text, paragraph inline children
     (emphasis + inline code), list item markers, fenced code language + body,
     and the link's visible text + URL target. Markdown -> HIR is the
     lossless direction (every structural attribute is preserved as a typed
     HIR entry), so these are exact structural asserts.

  2. Emits the HIR back to Markdown text and asserts the text is non-empty and
     begins with the heading sigil '#'.

  3. Re-parses the emitted Markdown back into HIR and asserts the re-parsed
     document is itself a document dictionary whose block-child sequence
     preserves the heading (level + text) and the fenced code block (language
     + body). Full byte/tree equality is NOT asserted because Markdown
     emission is intentionally lossy at the inline boundary (the lexer
     collapses an emphasis span into a single text slice on the second pass),
     so structural equality is checked only on the attributes the format
     round-trips faithfully.

Exit code: number of failed assertions (0 == all passed). No exit_with_code.
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/markdown/markdown_to_hir.runa" as MarkdownFrontend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/markdown/hir_to_markdown.runa" as MarkdownBackend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as TestUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: HIR dictionary readers (entry blocks are [key(0), value(8)])
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
The translation backends read attributes off HIR dictionary literals by
scanning the entries List and matching keys with string_equals; the probe
mirrors that exact access pattern so it validates the same memory layout the
production backend depends on. Returning the raw value node lets callers
decide whether to read it as a string literal, integer literal, or nested
collection.
@End Reasoning
Process called "dict_value_for_key" takes hir_dict as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Let entries be proc get_dictionary_entries from HIR with hir_dict

    If entries is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with entries
    Let index be 0

    While index is less than count:
        Let entry be proc get_at from List with entries, index
        Let current_key be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry, 0
        Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with key, current_key

        If matches is equal to 1:
            Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry, 8
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
String-typed attribute reader: locate the value node for a key and pull its
string payload via the canonical typed accessor, which returns 0 unless the
node really is a string-tagged HIR literal.
@End Reasoning
Process called "dict_string_for_key" takes hir_dict as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Let value_node be proc dict_value_for_key with hir_dict, key

    If value_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc get_string_literal_value from HIR with value_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Integer-typed attribute reader for the heading level. Locates the value node
and returns its int64 payload through the canonical typed accessor.
@End Reasoning
Process called "dict_integer_for_key" takes hir_dict as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Let value_node be proc dict_value_for_key with hir_dict, key

    If value_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc get_integer_literal_value from HIR with value_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Locates the first block child of a document (or any container) dictionary
whose "type" attribute equals the requested type string. Document children
are a HIR array literal of block dictionaries; this linear scan mirrors how a
renderer would dispatch on block kind.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_child_by_type" takes container_dict as Integer, type_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children_node be proc dict_value_for_key with container_dict, "children"

    If children_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let elements be proc get_list_elements from HIR with children_node

    If elements is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with elements
    Let index be 0

    While index is less than count:
        Let child be proc get_at from List with elements, index
        Let child_kind be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with child

        If child_kind is equal to HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL from HIR:
            Let child_type be proc dict_string_for_key with child, "type"

            If child_type is not equal to 0:
                Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with type_name, child_type

                If matches is equal to 1:
                    Return child
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Counts how many block children of a container carry the requested "type"
string. Used to assert the list-item count without assuming the items are
contiguous in the document child sequence.
@End Reasoning
Process called "count_children_by_type" takes container_dict as Integer, type_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children_node be proc dict_value_for_key with container_dict, "children"

    If children_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let elements be proc get_list_elements from HIR with children_node

    If elements is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with elements
    Let total be 0
    Let index be 0

    While index is less than count:
        Let child be proc get_at from List with elements, index
        Let child_kind be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with child

        If child_kind is equal to HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL from HIR:
            Let child_type be proc dict_string_for_key with child, "type"

            If child_type is not equal to 0:
                Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with type_name, child_type

                If matches is equal to 1:
                    Set total to total plus 1
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return total
End Process

@Reasoning:
Finds the first inline child of a paragraph (or other container) dictionary
whose "type" attribute equals the requested inline kind ("emphasis", "code",
"link", ...). Inline children mix bare HIR string literals (plain text runs)
and inline-element dictionaries; only dictionaries are inspected for a "type".
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_inline_by_type" takes container_dict as Integer, type_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children_node be proc dict_value_for_key with container_dict, "children"

    If children_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let elements be proc get_list_elements from HIR with children_node

    If elements is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with elements
    Let index be 0

    While index is less than count:
        Let child be proc get_at from List with elements, index
        Let child_kind be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with child

        If child_kind is equal to HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL from HIR:
            Let child_type be proc dict_string_for_key with child, "type"

            If child_type is not equal to 0:
                Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with type_name, child_type

                If matches is equal to 1:
                    Return child
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Probe entry point
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be proc create_test_results from TestUtils
    proc begin_suite from TestUtils with results, "Markdown translation round-trip"

    Note:
    Representative document: a level-2 ATX heading, a paragraph mixing
    emphasis and inline code, an unordered list with two items, a fenced code
    block with a language tag, and a link on its own paragraph. Block elements
    are separated by blank lines so the parser closes each block cleanly.
    :End Note
    Let source be "## Title Here\n\nText with *stress* and `code` here.\n\n- first item\n- second item\n\n```runa\nLet x be 1\n```\n\n[Runa](https://runa.dev)\n"

    Note: --- Stage 1: source -> HIR ---
    Let hir1 be proc markdown_to_hir_from_source from MarkdownFrontend with source
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "frontend produced HIR root", hir1

    Let root_kind be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with hir1
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "HIR root is dictionary literal", root_kind, HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL from HIR

    Let root_type be proc dict_string_for_key with hir1, "type"
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "root type is 'document'", root_type, "document"

    Let doc_children be proc dict_value_for_key with hir1, "children"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "document has children array", doc_children

    Let doc_children_kind be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with doc_children
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "document children is array literal", doc_children_kind, HIR_ARRAY_LITERAL from HIR

    Note: --- Heading: level 2 + exact text ---
    Let heading be proc find_child_by_type with hir1, "heading"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "document contains a heading block", heading

    Let heading_level be proc dict_integer_for_key with heading, "level"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "heading level is 2", heading_level, 2

    Let heading_text be proc dict_string_for_key with heading, "text"
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "heading text is 'Title Here'", heading_text, "Title Here"

    Note: --- Paragraph: emphasis + inline code inline children ---
    Let paragraph be proc find_child_by_type with hir1, "paragraph"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "document contains a paragraph block", paragraph

    Let emphasis be proc find_inline_by_type with paragraph, "emphasis"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "paragraph contains an emphasis inline", emphasis

    Let emphasis_text be proc dict_string_for_key with emphasis, "text"
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "emphasis text is 'stress'", emphasis_text, "stress"

    Let inline_code be proc find_inline_by_type with paragraph, "code"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "paragraph contains an inline code", inline_code

    Let inline_code_text be proc dict_string_for_key with inline_code, "text"
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "inline code text is 'code'", inline_code_text, "code"

    Note: --- List: two unordered items ---
    Let list_item_count be proc count_children_by_type with hir1, "list_item"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "document has 2 list items", list_item_count, 2

    Let first_item be proc find_child_by_type with hir1, "list_item"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "document contains a list item block", first_item

    Let first_item_list_type be proc dict_string_for_key with first_item, "list_type"
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "first list item is unordered", first_item_list_type, "unordered"

    Let first_item_marker be proc dict_string_for_key with first_item, "marker"
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "first list item marker is '-'", first_item_marker, "-"

    Note: --- Fenced code block: language tag + body ---
    Let code_block be proc find_child_by_type with hir1, "code_block"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "document contains a code block", code_block

    Let code_lang be proc dict_string_for_key with code_block, "language"
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "code block language is 'runa'", code_lang, "runa"

    Let code_body be proc dict_string_for_key with code_block, "code"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "code block has a code body", code_body

    Let code_body_len be proc string_length from StringCore with code_body
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "code block body is non-empty", code_body_len, 0

    Note: --- Link: visible text + URL target ---
    Let link be proc find_inline_by_type with paragraph, "link"
    Let link_para be paragraph

    If link is equal to 0:
        Note:
        The link sits in its own paragraph (separated by a blank line); scan
        every paragraph block for it.
        :End Note
        Let dchildren be proc dict_value_for_key with hir1, "children"
        Let delems be proc get_list_elements from HIR with dchildren
        Let dcount be proc size from List with delems
        Let di be 0

        While di is less than dcount:
            Let dblock be proc get_at from List with delems, di
            Let dblock_kind be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with dblock

            If dblock_kind is equal to HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL from HIR:
                Let dblock_type be proc dict_string_for_key with dblock, "type"

                If dblock_type is not equal to 0:
                    Let is_para be proc string_equals from StringCore with dblock_type, "paragraph"

                    If is_para is equal to 1:
                        Let candidate be proc find_inline_by_type with dblock, "link"

                        If candidate is not equal to 0:
                            Set link to candidate
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If

            Set di to di plus 1
        End While
    End If

    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "document contains a link inline", link

    Let link_text be proc dict_string_for_key with link, "text"
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "link text is 'Runa'", link_text, "Runa"

    Let link_url be proc dict_string_for_key with link, "url"
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "link url is 'https://runa.dev'", link_url, "https://runa.dev"

    Note: --- Stage 2: HIR -> Markdown text ---
    Let emitted be proc hir_to_markdown from MarkdownBackend with hir1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "backend produced Markdown text", emitted

    Let emitted_len be proc string_length from StringCore with emitted
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "emitted Markdown is non-empty", emitted_len, 0

    Let first_char be proc string_char_at from StringCore with emitted, 0
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "emitted Markdown begins with '#' (35)", first_char, 35

    Note: --- Stage 3: re-parse emitted Markdown -> HIR, assert stable structure ---
    Let hir2 be proc markdown_to_hir_from_source from MarkdownFrontend with emitted
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "re-parse of emitted Markdown produced HIR", hir2

    Let root2_type be proc dict_string_for_key with hir2, "type"
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "re-parsed root type is 'document'", root2_type, "document"

    Let heading2 be proc find_child_by_type with hir2, "heading"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "re-parsed document keeps a heading", heading2

    Let heading2_level be proc dict_integer_for_key with heading2, "level"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "re-parsed heading level is 2", heading2_level, 2

    Let heading2_text be proc dict_string_for_key with heading2, "text"
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "re-parsed heading text is 'Title Here'", heading2_text, "Title Here"

    Let code_block2 be proc find_child_by_type with hir2, "code_block"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "re-parsed document keeps a code block", code_block2

    Let code_lang2 be proc dict_string_for_key with code_block2, "language"
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "re-parsed code block language is 'runa'", code_lang2, "runa"

    proc print_summary from TestUtils with results
    Let failed be proc get_failed from TestUtils with results
    proc destroy_test_results from TestUtils with results

    Return failed
End Process
